What is ASMR? 
Autonomous sensory meridian response. It is a term used for an experience characterised by a static-like or tingling sensation on the skin that typically begins on the scalp and moves down the back of the neck and upper spine. It is most commonly triggered by specific acoustic, visual and digital media stimuli, and less commonly by intentional attentional control.
